Like if he is an addict, beats you
or does not give you an allowance.

22
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:48,859
Nothing like that.
He is a good, decent person.

23
00:01:49,026 --> 00:01:50,944
Then why do you want a divorce?

24
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:52,696
He won't come with me.

25
00:01:52,863 --> 00:01:56,950
If he does I'll cancel my request for a divorce.

26
00:01:57,868 --> 00:02:00,454
- Will you come?
- No, I won't.

27
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:03,373
- Why not, Your Honor?
- You know why.

28
00:02:03,457 --> 00:02:05,959
No, I don't. Please explain again why.

29
00:02:06,043 --> 00:02:08,962
Let her explain why we should
move abroad in these circumstances.

30
00:02:09,046 --> 00:02:11,465
- You give me one reason to stay.
- I'll give you a thousand.

31
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:15,302
- Just one.
- My father. I can't leave him.

32
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:16,470
But you can leave your wife?

33
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:19,222
- When did I leave you?
- You brought me here.

34
00:02:19,306 --> 00:02:20,307
You filed for a divorce.

35
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:23,435
When you tell your wife and child to leave,
isn't that leaving them?

36
00:02:23,518 --> 00:02:25,979
Your Honor, didn't he just say
leave if you want?

37
00:02:26,063 --> 00:02:27,439
Yes, and I'll say it again.

38
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:30,067
If you don't want to stay
I can't keep you by force.

39
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,152
Keep your voice down. Calm down.

40
00:02:32,235 --> 00:02:35,405
One day you came to live with me.
Today you don't.

41
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:38,158
- When you prefer...
- What does "you prefer" mean?

42
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:39,910
This was something we both started.

43
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:44,498
Your Honor, after 18 months of running
around and expenses, we got our visa.

44
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:48,335
It has been six months now
and it will expire in 40 days.

45
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:50,170
Why should we lose this opportunity?

46
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:54,841
You don't want to lose this opportunity,
then make a suggestion.

47
00:02:54,925 --> 00:02:56,009
You know my situation.

48
00:02:56,093 --> 00:02:58,136
Tell us what to do, Your Honor.

49
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:01,765
- His father is his excuse...
- He is not my excuse. He's the reason.

50
00:03:01,932 --> 00:03:03,684
- Let me speak.
- Calm down.

51
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,895
His father has Alzheimer's.
He doesn't even know that he's his son.

52
00:03:07,062 --> 00:03:11,400
- What difference does it make to him?
- Why are you saying that?

53
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:13,402
Does he even realize you are his son?

54
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:15,445
I know he is my father.

55
00:03:15,612 --> 00:03:18,740
Your daughter or her future is
not important to you?

56
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:22,619
Who said anything about our daughter?
Why do you think only you care?

57
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:26,373
So the children living in this country
don't have a future?

58
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:29,793
As a mother, I'd rather she didn't grow up
in these circumstances.

59
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,212
What circumstances?

60
00:03:33,797 --> 00:03:38,301
Is she better off here with both her parents
or there without a father?

61
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:41,138
That's why I want him to come.

62
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:43,306
I can't leave.

63
00:03:43,473 --> 00:03:45,767
How many times do I have to say it?

64
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:49,312
He can't come. So what happens to me?

65
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:51,648
Nothing. Go back to your life.

66
00:03:52,983 --> 00:03:55,068
If I could I wouldn't file for a divorce.

67
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:58,947
Consent has to be mutual.

68
00:03:59,114 --> 00:04:00,991
He just gave his.

69
00:04:01,158 --> 00:04:02,492
What circumstances?

70
00:04:02,576 --> 00:04:06,413
If she prefers to leave her family
to go live abroad, yes, I do.

71
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,415
He agrees.

72
00:04:08,582 --> 00:04:10,292
What about my daughter?

73
00:04:10,459 --> 00:04:13,670
You have to agree on everything.
How old is your daughter?

74
00:04:13,837 --> 00:04:15,922
Eleven in two weeks.

75
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:19,134
She can't leave
without her father's permission.

76
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:21,011
He won't give permission.

77
00:04:21,178 --> 00:04:22,971
That's between you two.

78
00:04:23,138 --> 00:04:25,974
Please sign here and good day.

79
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:27,934
Your Honor, I came here
for you to solve my problem.

80
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:29,519
Please sign here.

81
00:04:29,603 --> 00:04:30,604
You, too.

82
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:33,315
- Where should I sign?
- Here.

83
00:04:33,648 --> 00:04:36,610
He can have everything,
I just want my daughter.

84
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:40,530
Our daughter is attached to me.
She doesn't even want to go with you.

85
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:43,033
- She doesn't know better.
- Why not?

86
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,494
She is 11 years old.

87
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:48,622
Please sign here
and don't take the court's time.

88
00:04:48,789 --> 00:04:52,042
- No one knows better except you.
- No, you're the one who knows better.

89
00:04:53,502 --> 00:04:56,296
Your Honor, what should I do?
I only have 40 days.

90
00:04:56,463 --> 00:04:58,381
You can't file for a divorce
over every little problem.

91
00:04:58,548 --> 00:04:59,883
A little problem?

92
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:02,219
My problem is not little.

93
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:05,388
It is my daughter.

94
00:05:06,181 --> 00:05:08,642
She is his daughter, too. He has rights, too.

95
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:11,394
My finding is that your problem is
a small problem.

96
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:13,647
Please sign here and good day.

