- Dad!
- Quick!

264
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:30,206
Wait.

265
00:21:53,229 --> 00:21:54,230
Here.

266
00:21:56,065 --> 00:21:57,107
Keep it.

267
00:21:57,274 --> 00:21:58,275
Really?

268
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:15,668
Hello.

269
00:22:15,751 --> 00:22:16,961
- Any change?
- He didn't give it.

270
00:22:17,127 --> 00:22:18,128
Hello.

271
00:22:18,254 --> 00:22:22,258
- Hello, how are you?
- Fine, thank you.

272
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:25,469
I'll get my books.

273
00:22:26,053 --> 00:22:27,471
And your test results.

274
00:22:27,638 --> 00:22:29,807
- How are you, Ms. Qahraei?
- Fine, thanks, and you?

275
00:22:29,974 --> 00:22:31,767
Fine, thanks.

276
00:22:31,934 --> 00:22:33,310
Sorry we're late.

277
00:22:33,477 --> 00:22:35,229
It's okay. How's your wife?

278
00:22:35,396 --> 00:22:37,898
- Good, thank you.
- We'll get started.

279
00:22:39,316 --> 00:22:41,277
- Hello, sir.
- Hello.

280
00:22:42,111 --> 00:22:43,654
How are you, Dad?

281
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:46,282
- Hi, young lady.
- Hello.

282
00:22:46,782 --> 00:22:48,576
Here's the paper.

283
00:22:51,787 --> 00:22:54,748
Did you read the paper for him
or did he read it for you?

284
00:22:56,417 --> 00:22:57,626
Son...

285
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:00,296
Ali is married.

286
00:23:00,462 --> 00:23:02,506
- Who's Ali?
- Ali.

287
00:23:02,965 --> 00:23:05,009
Yeah, Ali's married. Termeh, hurry.

288
00:23:05,759 --> 00:23:07,761
His oxygen valve wasn't shut.

289
00:23:08,012 --> 00:23:10,097
He must've opened it.

290
00:23:10,264 --> 00:23:13,309
From tomorrow tighten it a bit more
so he can't open it.

291
00:23:13,475 --> 00:23:14,518
- Hi, young lady.
- Hello.

292
00:23:16,812 --> 00:23:18,147
I can't come anymore.

293
00:23:19,148 --> 00:23:21,191
Didn't we say every day?

294
00:23:21,442 --> 00:23:22,860
The commute is too much.

295
00:23:23,027 --> 00:23:26,322
I turned someone else away. It's 4:00.

296
00:23:27,031 --> 00:23:29,867
How can I find someone now
for tomorrow morning?

297
00:23:30,326 --> 00:23:31,493
It's too much work.

298
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:34,955
Really I can't. The work is heavy, I can't.

299
00:23:37,458 --> 00:23:39,501
Come to the other room, please.

300
00:23:41,128 --> 00:23:43,380
- Somayeh, where's your scarf?
- It's here.

301
00:23:45,299 --> 00:23:48,177
Maybe you're tired 'cause it's your first day.

302
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:49,553
No.

303
00:23:50,638 --> 00:23:53,057
You were here for a few minutes. You saw.

304
00:23:54,016 --> 00:23:56,060
Somayeh, come get your bag.

305
00:23:57,144 --> 00:23:59,521
Can you please give me that number?

306
00:24:02,858 --> 00:24:04,652
They also do ultrasounds.

307
00:24:05,069 --> 00:24:07,154
It moved a lot today.

308
00:24:07,655 --> 00:24:08,697
Then it's a boy.

309
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:11,909
It was kicking in Mommy's tummy.

310
00:24:13,494 --> 00:24:15,329
'Cause he wants to come out...

311
00:24:15,496 --> 00:24:17,039
To play with me.

312
00:24:22,878 --> 00:24:25,381
Can you write it in here, please?

313
00:24:26,715 --> 00:24:28,884
Tell them Qahraei sent you.

314
00:24:29,218 --> 00:24:30,886
They know me.

315
00:24:32,554 --> 00:24:34,932
- Is it a man or a woman?
- A woman.

316
00:24:35,099 --> 00:24:36,850
Call first.

317
00:24:37,559 --> 00:24:39,436
You had to tell me yesterday.

318
00:24:39,603 --> 00:24:42,398
How can I leave him
at home alone tomorrow?

319
00:24:43,607 --> 00:24:46,902
- Where does your mom keep the tea?
- I don't know.

320
00:24:47,069 --> 00:24:49,738
You should've told me I'd have to clean him.

321
00:24:49,905 --> 00:24:51,115
Clean him?

322
00:24:52,116 --> 00:24:53,701
He soiled his pants today.

323
00:24:58,747 --> 00:25:01,208
It's not right for me to clean him.

324
00:25:07,589 --> 00:25:10,259
Please pay me for today so I can go.

325
00:25:21,395 --> 00:25:23,147
He always said when he had to go.

326
00:25:25,399 --> 00:25:29,069
There are companies you can call
for a male helper.

327
00:25:29,903 --> 00:25:32,656
I can't just let anyone into my home.

328
00:25:34,283 --> 00:25:35,325
How can I leave him
at home alone tomorrow?

329
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:37,995
Count it, please.

330
00:25:38,162 --> 00:25:39,955
Sorry, but it's a religious issue.

331
00:25:40,122 --> 00:25:41,165
It's okay.

332
00:25:41,331 --> 00:25:43,292
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

333
00:25:43,459 --> 00:25:44,460
Bye.

334
00:25:44,626 --> 00:25:45,794
Good bye.

335
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:56,013
Yes?

336
00:25:56,096 --> 00:25:57,931
I wanted to know if it is okay for me

337
00:25:58,182 --> 00:26:00,809
to give your number to my husband

338
00:26:00,976 --> 00:26:02,936
and tell him I got it out of the paper.

339
00:26:03,103 --> 00:26:05,314
For the housework and your father.

340
00:26:05,481 --> 00:26:09,276
Give him the job description
and if he agrees tell him to come...

341
00:26:09,443 --> 00:26:11,487
I don't want to tell him I know you.

342
00:26:11,653 --> 00:26:13,155
I didn't tell him I was coming here.

343
00:26:14,281 --> 00:26:18,118
Then tell him to call me
or tell him to come here tonight.

344
00:26:18,285 --> 00:26:20,454
It's late for tonight.

345
00:26:20,621 --> 00:26:22,206
I'll come tomorrow.

346
00:26:22,831 --> 00:26:25,209
Just don't give the job to anyone else.

347
00:26:25,459 --> 00:26:27,461
You'll see with him for the money.

348
00:26:27,628 --> 00:26:30,839
That's not a problem. Tell him to call me.
I will arrange to meet him.

349
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:33,467
- Thank you.
- You're welcome. Bye.

350
00:26:33,842 --> 00:26:35,177
And thank you.

351
00:26:45,687 --> 00:26:47,189
Mr. Lavasani?

352
00:26:48,899 --> 00:26:50,150
Go ahead.

353
00:27:09,753 --> 00:27:11,713
Hello. I am Samadi.

354
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:13,757
- I called about the job.
- Yes, how are you?

355
00:27:13,924 --> 00:27:14,925
Sorry I'm late.

356
00:27:15,008 --> 00:27:17,511
It's okay. Where did you work before?

357
00:27:18,178 --> 00:27:19,388
I was a cobbler.

358
00:27:19,555 --> 00:27:21,723
And you're okay with cleaning him?

359
00:27:21,932 --> 00:27:23,058
With what?

360
00:27:23,267 --> 00:27:25,561
Since yesterday he's been soiling himself.

361
00:27:26,854 --> 00:27:29,064
I'll treat him like my own father.

362
00:27:29,439 --> 00:27:32,609
But you'll be alone with him
and you have to really watch him.

363
00:27:32,776 --> 00:27:33,944
Your wife won't be there?

364
00:27:34,444 --> 00:27:36,363
No, I am single for now.

365
00:27:39,032 --> 00:27:42,077
Excuse me but isn't 300,000
too little for this work?

366
00:27:42,744 --> 00:27:44,246
How much did you have in mind?

367
00:27:44,705 --> 00:27:46,248
Maybe if you could pay 400,000...

368
00:27:46,582 --> 00:27:48,083
I really can't pay that.

369
00:27:48,625 --> 00:27:49,918
I'll come for a few days.

370
00:27:50,085 --> 00:27:53,088
If you like my work,
add something to the 300,000.

371
00:27:53,255 --> 00:27:55,465
I'll treat him like my own father.

372
00:27:55,632 --> 00:27:56,967
I can even start today.

373
00:27:57,259 --> 00:28:01,096
No, there's someone there today.
Start tomorrow and bring an ID.

374
00:28:01,471 --> 00:28:02,723
Like what?

375
00:28:02,890 --> 00:28:05,893
Any legal ID will do.

376
00:28:06,852 --> 00:28:07,853
Pious?

377
00:28:07,936 --> 00:28:09,521
Worshipper.

378
00:28:09,938 --> 00:28:10,939
Barren?

379
00:28:11,273 --> 00:28:12,274
<i>Sandbar .</i>

380
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:13,859
Desert!

381
00:28:13,942 --> 00:28:14,943
Desert.

382
00:28:15,152 --> 00:28:16,153
Insurrection?

383
00:28:16,486 --> 00:28:17,654
Rebellion.

384
00:28:19,406 --> 00:28:20,407
Doorbell?

385
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:21,950
- Razieh.
- No!

386
00:28:22,242 --> 00:28:23,202
Her husband.

387
00:28:23,285 --> 00:28:24,328
Yes.

388
00:28:28,957 --> 00:28:31,919
Give the Persian version of
the following words...

389
00:28:32,085 --> 00:28:34,129
-"Maquette"?
- Nemunak.

390
00:28:34,463 --> 00:28:36,757
<i>-"Compote"?
- Khoshaab.</i>

391
00:28:36,840 --> 00:28:40,010
<i>-"Guarantee"?
- Tazmin, zemanat.</i>

392
00:28:40,093 --> 00:28:41,970
That's Arabic, not Persian.

393
00:28:42,137 --> 00:28:44,014
That's what my teacher said.

394
00:28:44,473 --> 00:28:45,766
Don't give me that.

395
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:50,312
What's wrong is wrong,
no matter who says what.

396
00:28:52,439 --> 00:28:55,317
- For "guarantee" write...
- She'll deduct points.

397
00:28:55,484 --> 00:28:56,526
That's okay, let her.

398
00:28:57,861 --> 00:28:59,488
<i>Write poshtvaneh.</i>

399
00:29:00,322 --> 00:29:01,657
<i>Poshtvaneh.</i>

400
00:29:10,499 --> 00:29:11,541
Hello.

401
00:29:19,508 --> 00:29:22,844
What happened?
Your husband was supposed to come today.

402
00:29:23,011 --> 00:29:24,513
Sorry, he couldn't make it.

403
00:29:25,138 --> 00:29:26,807
What about tomorrow?

404
00:29:27,182 --> 00:29:29,393
I don't know. If he doesn't I'll come.

405
00:29:29,559 --> 00:29:32,312
I hope he won't change his mind every day.

406
00:29:32,688 --> 00:29:34,564
No, poor guy wanted to come.

407
00:29:34,731 --> 00:29:38,986
Last night, one of his creditors came
with an officer and took him away.

408
00:29:39,194 --> 00:29:42,072
Yes, but if something comes up
and he can't make it,

409
00:29:42,322 --> 00:29:43,657
I need to know in advance.

410
00:29:43,824 --> 00:29:45,826
No, he will definitely come.

411
00:29:46,368 --> 00:29:50,706
I'll go see the creditor and beg him

412
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:52,416
to release him.

413
00:29:52,874 --> 00:29:55,210
Please lock the door behind me.

414
00:29:55,377 --> 00:29:56,586
Good bye.

415
00:30:36,585 --> 00:30:37,627
Hi.

416
00:30:45,802 --> 00:30:47,888
Don't step on it. It is dirty.

417
00:30:50,432 --> 00:30:52,309
Go take the garbage out.

418
00:30:55,103 --> 00:30:56,313
Can you?

419
00:30:57,481 --> 00:30:58,774
Yes.

420
00:31:18,085 --> 00:31:20,629
Where will I get you a clean dress?

421
00:31:22,798 --> 00:31:24,299
Take it off!

422
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:26,510
Take it off!

423
00:31:31,014 --> 00:31:32,182
Mommy,

424
00:31:32,682 --> 00:31:34,142
he's not in his room.

425
00:31:34,309 --> 00:31:36,603
- What?
- He's not in his room.

426
00:31:38,146 --> 00:31:39,981
Go look in the bathroom.

427
00:33:04,441 --> 00:33:05,484
Like that.

428
00:33:05,567 --> 00:33:08,111
Block the ball. Okay?

429
00:33:26,588 --> 00:33:27,589
Give me five.

430
00:33:29,090 --> 00:33:32,761
- Grandpa, whose side are you on?
- He's the manager.

431
00:33:40,769 --> 00:33:41,770
Did you see that?

432
00:34:05,293 --> 00:34:06,586
What's wrong?

433
00:34:07,295 --> 00:34:08,588
Sit here.

434
00:34:19,766 --> 00:34:20,976
You Okay?

435
00:34:38,702 --> 00:34:40,829
Where've you been?

436
00:34:40,996 --> 00:34:44,040
Poor thing has been waiting for half an hour.

437
00:34:44,457 --> 00:34:46,334
It's a long commute.

438
00:34:46,501 --> 00:34:47,544
Hello.

439
00:34:50,005 --> 00:34:52,382
Also, take the garbage outwith the bin.

440
00:34:53,008 --> 00:34:55,385
The bags tear and dirty the stairs.

441
00:34:55,552 --> 00:34:59,055
Yesterday I got dizzy.
I dropped the bag and it tore.

442
00:34:59,222 --> 00:35:00,682
I'll mop the stairs.

443
00:35:02,392 --> 00:35:03,560
Go in.

444
00:35:03,727 --> 00:35:05,186
Let us in.

445
00:35:11,151 --> 00:35:12,694
Let me close the door.

446
00:35:42,182 --> 00:35:44,225
- Mrs...
- She's not there?

447
00:35:45,393 --> 00:35:47,896
- What's her kid's name?
- Somayeh.

448
00:35:50,023 --> 00:35:52,776
Don't sit there. It's wet.

449
00:35:53,443 --> 00:35:54,736
Somayeh!

450
00:35:56,696 --> 00:35:58,031
Somayeh!

451
00:36:10,293 --> 00:36:11,753
Mrs. Kalani!

452
00:36:12,587 --> 00:36:14,047
Knock.

453
00:36:16,383 --> 00:36:17,717
Grandpa!

454
00:36:18,301 --> 00:36:19,761
Mrs. Kalani!

455
00:36:21,763 --> 00:36:22,889
Yes.

456
00:36:23,056 --> 00:36:24,766
- Hello, how are you?
- Fine, thanks.

457
00:36:24,933 --> 00:36:27,227
Did you see the lady that works for us?

458
00:36:27,394 --> 00:36:29,270
She was mopping the stairs.

459
00:36:29,437 --> 00:36:31,648
- When?
- Before noon.

460
00:36:31,898 --> 00:36:34,651
- She's not there?
- No. Thanks.

461
00:36:35,110 --> 00:36:37,904
Wait here. I'll get the keys from the car.

462
00:36:51,418 --> 00:36:53,128
What's wrong?

463
00:36:54,337 --> 00:36:55,338
Dad?

464
00:37:17,777 --> 00:37:19,154
Get his feet.

465
00:37:26,828 --> 00:37:28,997
Dad, get up, look at Termeh.

466
00:37:29,456 --> 00:37:30,457
Dad!

467
00:37:45,138 --> 00:37:46,514
He's breathing.

468
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:47,849
Don't worry.

469
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:02,572
Does your arm hurt?
Help me take his shirt off.

470
00:38:05,700 --> 00:38:07,076
Move your arm.

471
00:38:07,911 --> 00:38:09,412
Does it hurt?

472
00:38:12,916 --> 00:38:14,417
Take a step.

473
00:38:16,002 --> 00:38:17,253
Walk.

474
00:38:17,545 --> 00:38:19,714
Let's get the paper, Dad.

475
00:38:20,173 --> 00:38:21,549
Move your leg.

476
00:38:24,260 --> 00:38:27,764
Does it hurt? Let me see what's happened.

477
00:38:28,723 --> 00:38:30,683
Who did this to you?

478
00:38:32,727 --> 00:38:35,355
I want to see if your legs are okay.

479
00:38:37,232 --> 00:38:40,401
Let me... Honey, go to your room.

480
00:38:40,568 --> 00:38:43,238
- Has something happened?
- No. Go out.

481
00:38:45,365 --> 00:38:46,908
She's gone, Dad.

482
00:38:47,075 --> 00:38:49,577
Let me see your legs.

483
00:38:51,913 --> 00:38:53,248
Take them off.

484
00:39:13,434 --> 00:39:14,561
Scum!

485
00:39:18,064 --> 00:39:20,900
- Honey, did you take money from the drawer?
- No.

486
00:39:20,984 --> 00:39:22,735
Okay, go to the kitchen.

487
00:39:26,489 --> 00:39:29,659
I told you to go to the kitchen.

488
00:39:29,826 --> 00:39:32,245
You saw that nothing happened.

489
00:39:32,954 --> 00:39:35,832
Go on... Close the door.

490
00:40:07,155 --> 00:40:08,156
Hello.

491
00:40:10,950 --> 00:40:12,118
Come here.

492
00:40:13,661 --> 00:40:15,496
Mommy, I'm thirsty.

493
00:40:23,671 --> 00:40:24,672
Watch him.

494
00:40:27,133 --> 00:40:28,134
Hello.

495
00:40:29,010 --> 00:40:30,345
Where were you?

496
00:40:32,847 --> 00:40:35,850
Something came up. I had to go out.

497
00:40:36,059 --> 00:40:38,353
You had no right to go.

498
00:40:38,519 --> 00:40:41,731
- He was asleep.
- So you lock the door and leave?

499
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:45,693
I was gone briefly.

500
00:40:45,860 --> 00:40:48,738
Briefly? You're lying.

501
00:40:48,905 --> 00:40:51,074
He was dying when I got here!

502
00:40:51,240 --> 00:40:53,493
He always naps at this time so I...

503
00:40:53,660 --> 00:40:55,912
So you do this every day?

504
00:40:56,079 --> 00:40:58,539
Look the door and run your errands?

505
00:40:58,706 --> 00:41:00,541
No. I swear to God, today I had to.

506
00:41:00,708 --> 00:41:03,711
- Why did you tie his hand?
- Go wait outside.

507
00:41:06,214 --> 00:41:08,216
Was this our agreement?

508
00:41:08,383 --> 00:41:09,592
I had to go.

509
00:41:10,009 --> 00:41:12,011
I had no choice.

510
00:41:12,178 --> 00:41:13,554
Thanks a lot!

511
00:41:13,721 --> 00:41:15,932
You tie his hand every day

512
00:41:16,182 --> 00:41:17,725
and go do your own stuff.

513
00:41:17,892 --> 00:41:18,893
Is he okay?

514
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:21,562
Thanks a lot!

515
00:41:22,772 --> 00:41:24,399
Wait outside, sweetie.

516
00:41:24,565 --> 00:41:26,567
Go check on Grandpa.

517
00:41:29,028 --> 00:41:30,780
Why did you go in that room?

518
00:41:31,155 --> 00:41:32,156
Which room?

519
00:41:32,365 --> 00:41:35,743
Which room?
The one you took the money from.

520
00:41:36,369 --> 00:41:38,454
I took money from that room?

521
00:41:38,705 --> 00:41:40,915
- Don't I pay you?
- I took money?

522
00:41:41,082 --> 00:41:42,125
You didn't take it?

523
00:41:42,208 --> 00:41:44,419
I swear I didn't take any money.

524
00:41:44,585 --> 00:41:45,586
Get out.

525
00:41:46,462 --> 00:41:49,257
Sir, I'm swearing on our martyrs.

526
00:41:52,093 --> 00:41:54,595
You say I took money.

527
00:41:54,762 --> 00:41:58,933
Here, look in my bag.
If I took it, it should be here.

528
00:41:59,100 --> 00:42:00,268
Here, take this.

529
00:42:00,435 --> 00:42:02,937
Give me my bag.

530
00:42:04,439 --> 00:42:06,441
I am swearing on our martyrs
that I didn't go there.

531
00:42:06,607 --> 00:42:07,942
Here's my bag.

532
00:42:08,234 --> 00:42:09,652
What are you doing?

533
00:42:09,902 --> 00:42:10,903
I didn't go there.

534
00:42:10,987 --> 00:42:14,449
I'm swearing on our martyrs
that I didn't step into that room.

535
00:42:14,615 --> 00:42:16,617
- Get out.
- You're saying...

536
00:42:16,784 --> 00:42:20,121
What did I do? Don't touch me!

537
00:42:20,621 --> 00:42:22,623
I won't touch you. Get out.

538
00:42:24,292 --> 00:42:27,754
I won't leave till I get what I deserve!

539
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:30,631
What you deserve is for me to kick you out.

540
00:42:30,798 --> 00:42:33,760
Because of her I won't.

541
00:42:33,926 --> 00:42:37,764
Get out!
I'm doing you a favor by throwing you out.

542
00:42:37,972 --> 00:42:40,516
Tell me what's happened to him.

543
00:42:40,975 --> 00:42:42,685
It's my house, I want you out.

544
00:42:42,852 --> 00:42:45,313
Fine, but it's not right.

545
00:42:45,813 --> 00:42:47,774
- It displeases God.
- Out!

546
00:42:48,816 --> 00:42:50,318
That's it.

547
00:42:53,613 --> 00:42:54,655
Dad.

548
00:43:05,333 --> 00:43:07,960
Open the door. It's me. I want to come in...

549
00:43:09,629 --> 00:43:11,672
This is how you watch him?

550
00:43:15,551 --> 00:43:17,053
Open the door.

551
00:43:18,513 --> 00:43:20,556
Go check what's behind you.

552
00:43:21,015 --> 00:43:22,183
Have a look.

553
00:43:23,851 --> 00:43:24,811
Open the door!

554
00:43:24,894 --> 00:43:27,188
It's no use shouting.

555
00:43:28,147 --> 00:43:30,858
This is why I asked you to watch him.

556
00:43:31,025 --> 00:43:33,653
Maybe his leg hurts and he can't get up.

557
00:43:34,529 --> 00:43:36,572
Grandpa...

558
00:43:38,741 --> 00:43:41,077
Dad, open the door.

559
00:43:41,869 --> 00:43:43,996
Open the door, please.

560
00:43:45,748 --> 00:43:48,167
I'm going to push the door open.

561
00:43:48,334 --> 00:43:51,879
It'll hit you, Dad. Move aside.

562
00:43:53,881 --> 00:43:56,843
I'm going to push the door open.

563
00:43:59,554 --> 00:44:02,390
Why do you do this to yourself?

564
00:44:15,194 --> 00:44:16,571
Who told you to come in?

565
00:44:16,737 --> 00:44:19,532
- What happened to him?
- Give me the key. Get out!

566
00:44:19,699 --> 00:44:20,908
I didn't steal from you.

567
00:44:21,075 --> 00:44:22,785
You are pissing me off!

568
00:44:22,869 --> 00:44:23,828
I didn't.

569
00:44:23,911 --> 00:44:27,707
- Don't give me that!
- I wouldn't be here now if I had.

570
00:44:27,874 --> 00:44:28,875
Get out.

571
00:44:28,958 --> 00:44:30,459
Pay me for today.

572
00:44:30,585 --> 00:44:33,588
You already took your pay, didn't you?

573
00:44:34,297 --> 00:44:38,426
Since 5:30 this morning
with my daughter... Somayeh!

574
00:44:38,718 --> 00:44:39,927
Sir, wait!

575
00:44:40,094 --> 00:44:41,429
Get out.

576
00:44:41,596 --> 00:44:45,099
I swear I didn't steal.

577
00:44:45,266 --> 00:44:46,767
Get out!

578
00:44:59,572 --> 00:45:00,573
What happened?

579
00:45:05,411 --> 00:45:06,746
What happened?

580
00:45:07,121 --> 00:45:08,456
Sit.

581
00:45:16,005 --> 00:45:17,506
What happened?

582
00:45:20,927 --> 00:45:22,803
Mommy, be careful.

583
00:46:34,667 --> 00:46:36,544
Tell her to work with you on your English.

584
00:46:36,711 --> 00:46:37,837
Bye, Grandpa.

585
00:46:38,587 --> 00:46:40,756
Dad, Termeh said bye.

586
00:46:44,510 --> 00:46:45,594
Careful!

587
00:46:51,350 --> 00:46:52,435
Okay.

588
00:46:55,521 --> 00:46:56,605
What is it?

589
00:46:56,772 --> 00:46:58,107
Mom says come in.

590
00:46:59,191 --> 00:47:00,943
Tell her Grandpa's in the car.

591
00:47:01,110 --> 00:47:02,361
She says it's important.

592
00:47:05,531 --> 00:47:08,951
Not divorced yet and already ignoring us!

593
00:47:09,118 --> 00:47:10,578
I'm busy.

594
00:47:10,953 --> 00:47:14,081
People divorce their wives to get less busy.

595
00:47:14,248 --> 00:47:17,126
Ma'am, these channels have too much static.

596
00:47:17,293 --> 00:47:19,253
Okay, set the ones you can.

597
00:47:20,546 --> 00:47:22,590
- Come and sit.
- Thank you. Simin...

598
00:47:27,928 --> 00:47:28,929
Hi.

599
00:47:31,766 --> 00:47:33,267
Where's Termeh?

600
00:47:33,893 --> 00:47:35,269
In the car with dad.

601
00:47:35,478 --> 00:47:37,104
Then bring him in, too.

602
00:47:37,480 --> 00:47:38,939
No, he is tired.

603
00:47:39,106 --> 00:47:40,399
It's his nap time.

604
00:47:42,276 --> 00:47:43,277
What is it?

605
00:47:43,944 --> 00:47:45,613
Did you have a fight with that woman?

606
00:47:46,822 --> 00:47:47,907
Did she come see you?

607
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:49,158
Her sister-in-law called.

608
00:47:49,950 --> 00:47:51,619
Shameless!

609
00:47:51,786 --> 00:47:52,953
What did she do?

610
00:47:53,120 --> 00:47:56,499
Tied the old man to the bed
and locked the door.

611
00:47:56,665 --> 00:47:58,334
Went after her own errands.

612
00:47:58,793 --> 00:48:01,337
If I'd gotten there 10 minutes later,
I would've lost him.

613
00:48:01,420 --> 00:48:02,713
Is he okay?

614
00:48:02,797 --> 00:48:04,006
He had fallen off the bed.

615
00:48:04,173 --> 00:48:06,634
I don't know for how long he was like that.

616
00:48:07,009 --> 00:48:08,052
Where had she gone?

617
00:48:08,135 --> 00:48:09,136
How should I know?

618
00:48:09,845 --> 00:48:10,971
She said you hit her.

619
00:48:11,514 --> 00:48:12,556
I hit her?

620
00:48:13,099 --> 00:48:15,601
- Nonsense.
- Then why is she in the hospital?

621
00:48:17,937 --> 00:48:19,814
Hospital? Why?

622
00:48:20,648 --> 00:48:22,024
You're asking me?

623
00:48:22,274 --> 00:48:23,776
I just pushed her out of the house.

624
00:48:23,943 --> 00:48:26,195
The sister-in-law called and told me off.

625
00:48:26,987 --> 00:48:27,988
Saying what?

626
00:48:28,197 --> 00:48:30,950
That if she dies,
her blood will be on your hands.

627
00:48:32,993 --> 00:48:33,994
Stuff like that.

628
00:48:35,704 --> 00:48:40,543
- She didn't say what happened?
- I hung up. She started cursing.

629
00:48:43,546 --> 00:48:46,632
That's what you get
for hiring people off the streets.

630
00:48:46,799 --> 00:48:51,053
Don't blame me.
I told you I only know her sister-in-law.

631
00:48:51,220 --> 00:48:53,013
Did she say which hospital?

632
00:48:58,519 --> 00:48:59,687
- Hello.
- Yes?

633
00:49:00,688 --> 00:49:01,856
Hold, please.

634
00:49:02,356 --> 00:49:05,901
A woman by the name of Razieh was
brought in tonight.

635
00:49:06,235 --> 00:49:09,697
- What's her family name?
- I don't know. She was admitted earlier.

636
00:49:09,864 --> 00:49:11,031
Why was she brought in?

637
00:49:11,198 --> 00:49:13,993
- They just told us...
- That she was taken to hospital.

638
00:49:14,493 --> 00:49:16,871
I'll call you back. Bye.

639
00:49:17,204 --> 00:49:20,166
Her husband's last name is Samadi.

640
00:49:24,378 --> 00:49:26,005
Razieh Asnaqi?

641
00:49:26,547 --> 00:49:28,716
Is she in her thirties?

642
00:49:31,051 --> 00:49:32,720
She had surgery. She's in post-op.

643
00:49:33,220 --> 00:49:34,305
Why surgery?

644
00:49:35,347 --> 00:49:36,599
She had a miscarriage.

645
00:49:40,519 --> 00:49:41,604
Is she okay now?

646
00:49:41,687 --> 00:49:42,938
Hello? Hold.

647
00:49:43,022 --> 00:49:44,023
Yes.

648
00:49:44,106 --> 00:49:46,942
Is her family here?

649
00:49:47,193 --> 00:49:48,360
If they are, they are downstairs.

650
00:49:48,903 --> 00:49:50,196
Thank you.

651
00:49:57,536 --> 00:49:59,246
What did you do to her?

652
00:50:01,081 --> 00:50:02,625
What did I do to her?

653
00:50:23,229 --> 00:50:24,230
Why surgery?

654
00:50:28,108 --> 00:50:29,610
- How are you?
- Fine, thanks.

655
00:50:29,818 --> 00:50:30,945
Hello, ma'am.

656
00:50:31,320 --> 00:50:32,321
How is she?

657
00:50:32,947 --> 00:50:33,948
Who?

658
00:50:34,615 --> 00:50:35,824
Your wife.

659
00:50:37,117 --> 00:50:38,827
They took her to the ward.

660
00:50:40,329 --> 00:50:41,622
Do you know her?

661
00:50:41,789 --> 00:50:43,958
- I know her.
- My wife.

662
00:50:44,291 --> 00:50:46,794
- They didn't have sandwiches.
- Hello.

663
00:50:53,259 --> 00:50:54,927
Can we see her?

664
00:50:55,094 --> 00:50:57,012
Where do you know her from?

665
00:50:57,304 --> 00:51:01,308
Your sister introduced her to us
for housework.

666
00:51:01,517 --> 00:51:03,102
Thanks a lot!

667
00:51:05,604 --> 00:51:06,981
She was coming to your house to work?

668
00:51:07,439 --> 00:51:08,816
She came for a few days.

669
00:51:09,483 --> 00:51:12,486
Apparently you couldn't come
so she came in your place.

670
00:51:12,695 --> 00:51:14,363
Come sit and eat something.

671
00:51:14,655 --> 00:51:17,658
You mean she took care of your father?

672
00:51:17,992 --> 00:51:19,618
Just for a few days.

673
00:51:20,160 --> 00:51:21,495
Two or three days.

674
00:51:21,662 --> 00:51:24,331
Why didn't you tell me this at the bank?

675
00:51:26,709 --> 00:51:28,711
I thought she would tell you.

676
00:51:29,962 --> 00:51:31,714
Why have you come here now?

677
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:33,799
To see if we can do something.

678
00:51:33,966 --> 00:51:34,967
Do what?

679
00:51:35,134 --> 00:51:37,636
Help. We were worried.

680
00:51:37,803 --> 00:51:39,346
Did she fall?

681
00:51:40,014 --> 00:51:42,474
Come with me. I'll explain.

682
00:51:43,309 --> 00:51:45,853
I'll explain to you... Come with me.

683
00:51:46,353 --> 00:51:48,522
I understand your situation.

684
00:51:48,689 --> 00:51:51,692
You kill her child
and now you've come to do what?

685
00:51:51,859 --> 00:51:52,985
I'm really sorry.

686
00:51:53,152 --> 00:51:55,654
I'm sorry won't be a child to her.

687
00:51:55,863 --> 00:51:57,364
Just tell me one thing.

688
00:51:57,531 --> 00:51:58,991
I'll explain outside.

689
00:51:59,366 --> 00:52:01,869
Wait! Why didn't you tell me that day?

690
00:52:02,328 --> 00:52:04,079
I told you. I thought she...

691
00:52:07,416 --> 00:52:09,918
You live alone in that house.

692
00:52:11,879 --> 00:52:13,547
Let him go.

693
00:52:14,381 --> 00:52:15,883
Calm down.

694
00:52:16,925 --> 00:52:19,219
This is a hospital.

695
00:52:20,888 --> 00:52:22,181
Don't!

696
00:52:22,348 --> 00:52:23,349
Stop!

697
00:52:27,770 --> 00:52:29,855
Why the hell did you come here?

698
00:52:33,275 --> 00:52:34,860
Let me see.

699
00:52:35,402 --> 00:52:37,655
- My own sister?
- I'm sorry.

700
00:52:37,738 --> 00:52:38,781
Forgive me.

701
00:52:38,864 --> 00:52:39,865
Let me see.

702
00:52:43,744 --> 00:52:45,704
Come out here.

703
00:52:47,414 --> 00:52:48,415
I want to talk to you.

704
00:52:51,460 --> 00:52:53,587
Please, I beg you. Hojjat!

705
00:53:01,303 --> 00:53:04,098
Do you want your seat down?

706
00:53:04,431 --> 00:53:05,432
No.

707
00:53:06,809 --> 00:53:10,104
I'll take you home
then I'll get Dad and Termeh.

708
00:53:11,772 --> 00:53:12,981
Let me see.

709
00:53:14,441 --> 00:53:15,776
No?

710
00:53:16,985 --> 00:53:19,738
You want to go to your parents' like this?

711
00:53:21,448 --> 00:53:24,159
It's over. You're coming home tonight.

712
00:53:27,246 --> 00:53:28,288
I don't want to.

713
00:53:38,632 --> 00:53:40,134
Where are you going?

714
00:53:47,474 --> 00:53:48,517
Cell phone.

715
00:53:50,102 --> 00:53:51,478
Hand it in.

716
00:55:00,714 --> 00:55:02,883
Did you hear his complaint?

717
00:55:03,050 --> 00:55:04,259
It was the 13th.

718
00:55:05,344 --> 00:55:07,930
I'm sorry. I was really upset when I heard.

719
00:55:08,180 --> 00:55:10,682
- I went to the hospital.
- Then you admit it.

720
00:55:12,267 --> 00:55:13,977
Is this the medical examiner's report?

721
00:55:14,061 --> 00:55:18,524
It is the hospital report that we took

722
00:55:18,690 --> 00:55:20,692
to the medical examiner.

723
00:55:20,859 --> 00:55:22,486
Four and half months, male.

724
00:55:22,569 --> 00:55:23,904
Please explain.

725
00:55:24,363 --> 00:55:26,573
I accept that I was a bit rough.

726
00:55:26,740 --> 00:55:28,408
By rough you mean you pushed her?

727
00:55:28,617 --> 00:55:31,620
No. I tried to get her out of my house.

728
00:55:32,746 --> 00:55:35,290
Be clear. Your charge is murder.

729
00:55:36,458 --> 00:55:39,127
It was 19 weeks old. A full human being.

730
00:55:40,754 --> 00:55:43,131
I didn't intend to push her.

731
00:55:43,298 --> 00:55:45,592
I wanted her to leave
so I could close the door.

732
00:55:45,759 --> 00:55:47,719
- You didn't push me?
- Ma'am, please.

733
00:55:47,928 --> 00:55:50,138
If I knew she were pregnant,

734
00:55:50,305 --> 00:55:53,767
I wouldn't even have tried to get
her out of the house.

735
00:55:54,393 --> 00:55:56,270
I just wanted to close the door.

736
00:55:56,645 --> 00:55:58,272
Do you accept his explanation?

737
00:55:58,438 --> 00:56:02,317
He didn't push. He grabbed me here
and threw me and I fell on the stairs.

738
00:56:02,568 --> 00:56:04,611
I didn't throw you.

739
00:56:04,778 --> 00:56:07,447
I wanted to get you out of my house.

740
00:56:07,656 --> 00:56:10,576
- Who throws out a pregnant woman?
- I didn't know.

741
00:56:10,784 --> 00:56:11,827
Why are you lying?

742
00:56:11,910 --> 00:56:14,121
I found out in the hospital.

743
00:56:14,746 --> 00:56:17,291
Your Honor, can't everyone tell

744
00:56:17,499 --> 00:56:20,627
from the body of a woman
that she is pregnant?

745
00:56:21,128 --> 00:56:22,129
Four to five months pregnant.

746
00:56:22,337 --> 00:56:24,006
When would I even see you?

747
00:56:24,256 --> 00:56:27,259
I was already gone
or leaving when she'd come.

748
00:56:27,426 --> 00:56:30,345
When I'd come, she looked like this.

749
00:56:30,512 --> 00:56:32,848
Always with the chador.

750
00:56:33,015 --> 00:56:34,766
How can anyone tell she was pregnant?

751
00:56:34,933 --> 00:56:37,102
He can claim that he couldn't guess.

752
00:56:37,603 --> 00:56:41,481
I didn't think a pregnant woman
would come for this kind of work.

753
00:56:42,774 --> 00:56:45,861
Your Honor, I spoke of my pregnancy

754
00:56:46,111 --> 00:56:49,323
in front of him, his daughter and her tutor.

755
00:56:49,531 --> 00:56:51,617
They all heard it.

756
00:56:51,783 --> 00:56:53,660
When? I don't remember.

757
00:56:53,827 --> 00:56:55,704
No, of course you wouldn't remember.

758
00:56:55,871 --> 00:56:58,665
The issue isn't that I knew or not.

759
00:56:58,874 --> 00:57:00,375
Yes.

760
00:57:00,626 --> 00:57:02,294
If it's proven that you knew,

761
00:57:02,461 --> 00:57:04,838
the court can request
a prison term of one to three years.

762
00:57:08,050 --> 00:57:09,509
- Well?
- What?

763
00:57:10,552 --> 00:57:12,179
No, I didn't know.

764
00:57:12,346 --> 00:57:15,390
His daughter's tutor can testify.

765
00:57:15,557 --> 00:57:16,975
Can she come in tomorrow?

766
00:57:17,142 --> 00:57:19,519
I don't want her or the school involved.

767
00:57:19,686 --> 00:57:22,022
It's not good for my daughter.

768
00:57:22,189 --> 00:57:24,858
You trash. You've killed my child.

769
00:57:25,025 --> 00:57:26,360
It's bad for your child?

770
00:57:26,526 --> 00:57:30,113
She matters but ours was an animal?

771
00:57:30,197 --> 00:57:34,868
- Don't insult...
- Am I insulting? He took my pregnant wife...

772
00:57:35,077 --> 00:57:36,370
Quiet or I'll put you in prison.

773
00:57:36,870 --> 00:57:39,373
Please, he's a bit hot-tempered.

774
00:57:40,374 --> 00:57:42,542
Hot-tempered?

775
00:57:42,751 --> 00:57:47,506
I should sue you for working for
a single man we don't even know.

776
00:57:47,714 --> 00:57:51,551
I wanted to help with the bills.
He hasn't worked for months.

777
00:57:52,344 --> 00:57:54,888
The tutor has to come in as a witness.

778
00:57:55,097 --> 00:57:57,724
Call her to come in tomorrow.

779
00:58:00,352 --> 00:58:03,689
Your Honor, I'm here today for one thing.

780
00:58:04,189 --> 00:58:07,067
I lost my child but it didn't hurt as much

781
00:58:07,234 --> 00:58:10,070
as when he accused me of being a thief.

782
00:58:10,237 --> 00:58:11,321
We're thieves?

783
00:58:11,405 --> 00:58:12,823
If we were thieves,

784
00:58:12,906 --> 00:58:16,243
we wouldn't come to wipe your father's ass.

785
00:58:16,410 --> 00:58:18,912
Do you have proof that she stole?

786
00:58:19,079 --> 00:58:20,414
I didn't say she stole.

787
00:58:20,789 --> 00:58:23,083
Money was missing

788
00:58:23,542 --> 00:58:26,044
and it was the same amount that I pay her.

789
00:58:26,253 --> 00:58:27,254
Is that why you fought?

790
00:58:27,546 --> 00:58:29,047
He accused her of stealing.

791
00:58:29,256 --> 00:58:32,092
Your Honor, my father has Alzheimer's.

792
00:58:32,592 --> 00:58:36,388
She tied his hand to the bed
and left the house.

793
00:58:36,763 --> 00:58:38,265
That day I came home early.

794
00:58:38,432 --> 00:58:41,143
I saw him on the floor with his hand tied.

795
00:58:41,393 --> 00:58:42,769
I thought he had died.

796
00:58:43,437 --> 00:58:47,774
She came back
and I'm not saying I wasn't angry,

797
00:58:47,858 --> 00:58:48,859
I was.

798
00:58:48,942 --> 00:58:51,611
I told her to leave and she wouldn't.

799
00:58:51,820 --> 00:58:53,780
Where should I have gone?

800
00:58:53,947 --> 00:58:55,449
He accused me of stealing.

801
00:58:55,615 --> 00:58:58,243
If I hadn't asked for the money and left,

802
00:58:58,410 --> 00:59:00,579
he would've thought I had stolen.

803
00:59:00,787 --> 00:59:02,122
Sit down.

804
00:59:02,581 --> 00:59:04,624
- Was your father hurt?
- Yes, he was.

805
00:59:04,833 --> 00:59:08,462
How hurt?
If he had been, he would've filed a complaint.

806
00:59:08,628 --> 00:59:09,963
Yes, he was hurt.

807
00:59:10,130 --> 00:59:11,590
Where are you going?

808
00:59:11,757 --> 00:59:15,010
I'm going to check on my child.

809
00:59:15,343 --> 00:59:16,386
Come back quick.

810
00:59:16,636 --> 00:59:17,971
Close the door.

811
01:00:01,556 --> 01:00:02,682
What's taking so long?

812
01:00:03,767 --> 01:00:06,853
I'm not well. You go, I'll come.

813
01:00:07,062 --> 01:00:08,855
He says you locked up his father and left.

814
01:00:10,857 --> 01:00:11,858
What should I say?

815
01:00:12,359 --> 01:00:14,611
Say? If he complains you'll be charged.

816
01:00:16,780 --> 01:00:18,281
Where's Somayeh?

817
01:00:18,865 --> 01:00:19,950
Over there.

818
01:00:20,200 --> 01:00:22,035
Go. I'll get her and come.

819
01:00:22,619 --> 01:00:23,870
Let's go.

820
01:00:41,221 --> 01:00:42,389
Yes?

821
01:00:44,391 --> 01:00:47,477
He was sleeping.
I locked the door to keep him in.

822
01:00:47,894 --> 01:00:52,107
Even he would look the door
and leave me the key.

823
01:00:52,274 --> 01:00:53,650
I saw that he does it so I...

824
01:00:53,817 --> 01:00:55,819
He says you tied him to the bed.

825
01:00:58,655 --> 01:01:02,450
I was afraid he would wake up
and do something to himself.

826
01:01:02,617 --> 01:01:05,662
I was afraid for him.

827
01:01:05,912 --> 01:01:08,123
Why did you leave?

828
01:01:08,290 --> 01:01:10,333
- So you should hit her?
- Quiet!

829
01:01:10,584 --> 01:01:12,419
Who said you could touch my wife?

830
01:01:12,502 --> 01:01:13,587
Sir, get out.

831
01:01:13,670 --> 01:01:16,089
They don't care about honor, I do.

832
01:01:16,423 --> 01:01:18,967
- Don't be offensive.
- Leave the room.

833
01:01:22,429 --> 01:01:24,347
I want to file a complaint against this woman.

834
01:01:24,472 --> 01:01:25,515
Write your complaint.

835
01:01:25,765 --> 01:01:29,352
Take your father to the medical examiner.
If he's hurt get a report.

836
01:01:29,519 --> 01:01:31,271
What happens to our complaint?

837
01:01:31,688 --> 01:01:33,356
Sign this and leave.

838
01:01:33,690 --> 01:01:35,358
You have to post bail.

839
01:01:35,483 --> 01:01:36,776
What for?

840
01:01:37,277 --> 01:01:39,821
You're charged with murder.

841
01:01:39,988 --> 01:01:41,990
I can't let you leave.

842
01:01:42,157 --> 01:01:44,701
The blood money is 40 million.

843
01:01:44,868 --> 01:01:46,995
How am I going to post bail?

844
01:01:47,621 --> 01:01:51,124
I live at my dad's. He has Alzheimer's.

845
01:01:51,499 --> 01:01:53,376
If you don't you'll go to jail.

846
01:01:53,543 --> 01:01:56,713
My father can't even come here.

847
01:01:56,963 --> 01:01:58,381
He's sick.

848
01:01:58,548 --> 01:01:59,799
Please don't.

849
01:01:59,966 --> 01:02:02,385
I can't go to jail.

850
01:02:02,636 --> 01:02:04,888
I've left him at home to come here.

851
01:02:05,388 --> 01:02:07,307
I can't go to jail.

852
01:02:07,474 --> 01:02:08,808
I can't post bail.

853
01:02:08,975 --> 01:02:10,602
It's not in my hands. It's the law.

854
01:02:10,685 --> 01:02:11,895
Wait one second.

855
01:02:11,978 --> 01:02:14,689
What should I do with my dad?

856
01:02:14,898 --> 01:02:18,151
I left him at home
and locked the door to come here.

857
01:02:18,318 --> 01:02:19,903
My child will come home from school.

858
01:02:20,070 --> 01:02:21,363
Please. What are you writing?

859
01:02:21,488 --> 01:02:24,324
Don't waste time. Go make your call.

860
01:02:24,491 --> 01:02:26,534
I can't go to jail. I won't go.

861
01:02:27,077 --> 01:02:28,495
Write what you want!

862
01:02:28,703 --> 01:02:29,746
Go get an officer.

863
01:02:30,163 --> 01:02:31,873
What for? Don't.

864
01:02:32,040 --> 01:02:34,501
I'm begging you.

865
01:02:34,668 --> 01:02:36,503
Please don't write it.

866
01:02:37,254 --> 01:02:40,090
My life will be ruined.

867
01:02:40,257 --> 01:02:42,676
Don't waste time. Go make your call.

868
01:02:45,512 --> 01:02:49,391
<i>Hello, Termeh. I'm stuck here.
They're keeping me tonight.</i>

869
01:02:49,557 --> 01:02:53,561
<i>Don't worry. It's nothing.
But you'll be alone tonight.</i>

870
01:02:53,728 --> 01:02:57,691
<i>Take care of the house.
Take Grandpa to the bathroom regularly.</i>

871
01:02:57,857 --> 01:03:00,026
<i>Take care of yourself. I'll call you tomorrow.</i>

872
01:03:32,767 --> 01:03:36,396
If you hadn't left, Dad wouldn't be in jail.

873
01:03:36,563 --> 01:03:38,940
Your dad's not in jail because of me.

874
01:03:39,941 --> 01:03:41,735
He hit a pregnant woman.

875
01:03:41,901 --> 01:03:43,486
She came 'cause you left.

876
01:03:44,321 --> 01:03:46,448
How upset he was that I left.

877
01:03:47,240 --> 01:03:49,576
He knew you weren't really leaving.

878
01:03:50,910 --> 01:03:52,495
Did you tell him?

879
01:03:52,579 --> 01:03:53,955
No, he knew.

880
01:03:54,998 --> 01:03:56,166
Tell me the truth.

881
01:03:56,333 --> 01:03:57,751
You told him?

882
01:04:05,508 --> 01:04:08,345
Get your stuff. We're going to Grandma's.

883
01:04:08,428 --> 01:04:09,679
What about Grandpa?

884
01:04:09,763 --> 01:04:11,056
We'll take him, 1100.

885
01:04:11,139 --> 01:04:13,183
I have homework. I'm not coming.

886
01:04:13,975 --> 01:04:16,519
- You'll be on your own...
- Fine.

887
01:04:17,771 --> 01:04:20,440
You'd better not call.

888
01:04:31,868 --> 01:04:34,662
He doesn't even ask me to stay.

889
01:04:35,205 --> 01:04:37,123
He doesn't refuse to divorce.

890
01:04:37,665 --> 01:04:41,294
After having lived together for 14 years.

891
01:05:23,253 --> 01:05:24,254
Dad!

892
01:05:27,006 --> 01:05:29,008
What are you doing here?

893
01:05:30,176 --> 01:05:31,678
Who are you with?

894
01:05:32,887 --> 01:05:35,348
Didn't you have an exam?

895
01:05:35,515 --> 01:05:37,183
No, it's tomorrow.

896
01:05:37,892 --> 01:05:39,519
Who are you with?

897
01:05:44,065 --> 01:05:45,191
Hello.

898
01:05:46,025 --> 01:05:48,528
Shouldn't you tell us you're in trouble

899
01:05:48,611 --> 01:05:50,363
so we can bail you out?

900
01:05:50,530 --> 01:05:52,198
I didn't want to trouble you.

901
01:05:52,365 --> 01:05:53,908
Silly man.

902
01:05:54,117 --> 01:05:56,119
- Sit.
- No, ma'am, he has a hearing.

903
01:06:00,123 --> 01:06:01,583
Who are you with?

904
01:06:01,708 --> 01:06:03,209
He's safe.

905
01:06:03,710 --> 01:06:06,254
What are they saying?

906
01:06:06,921 --> 01:06:10,216
"My child" as if their 18-year old son

907
01:06:10,383 --> 01:06:12,218
was stabbed to death.

908
01:06:12,385 --> 01:06:13,720
Did you speak to them?

909
01:06:13,887 --> 01:06:16,556
You can't even speak to the man.

910
01:06:16,723 --> 01:06:19,267
I told the wife, "You're young.

911
01:06:19,601 --> 01:06:21,311
"You can try next year."

912
01:06:24,898 --> 01:06:25,899
What happened?

913
01:06:25,982 --> 01:06:28,985
- I have to appraise the house.
- Okay, go.

914
01:06:29,152 --> 01:06:30,445
Hi.

915
01:06:30,778 --> 01:06:33,072
- I'll be back.
- We'll be here.

916
01:06:38,745 --> 01:06:39,954
Thanks.

917
01:06:42,916 --> 01:06:44,584
- Hi, Mrs. Lavasani.
- Hi, how are you?

918
01:06:44,751 --> 01:06:45,835
Good, you?

919
01:06:46,002 --> 01:06:49,297
- Sorry we're troubling you.
- No, what trouble?

920
01:06:49,464 --> 01:06:53,009
Is it true what they're saying?

921
01:06:53,176 --> 01:06:56,429
Yes, unfortunately he pushed her
and she fell and lost her baby.

922
01:06:57,138 --> 01:06:58,348
So what should I tell them?

923
01:06:58,932 --> 01:07:01,476
I don't know what they'll ask.

924
01:07:01,643 --> 01:07:04,687
What if he asks something
to his disadvantage?

925
01:07:06,272 --> 01:07:08,608
I think you should tell the truth.

926
01:07:08,691 --> 01:07:09,859
Please don't stand there.

927
01:07:10,485 --> 01:07:11,694
Where was he?

928
01:07:11,861 --> 01:07:13,863
Mr. Lavasani was in the kitchen.

929
01:07:14,030 --> 01:07:17,325
He didn't have a reaction
to your conversation?

930
01:07:17,492 --> 01:07:18,618
If he did I didn't notice.

931
01:07:19,202 --> 01:07:21,204
How did you realize she was pregnant?

932
01:07:22,288 --> 01:07:23,998
I think she told me.

933
01:07:24,624 --> 01:07:26,334
You asked. Why should I tell you?

934
01:07:28,294 --> 01:07:32,173
Her daughter was drawing
a man and a woman.

935
01:07:32,340 --> 01:07:33,633
She said this is my mommy and daddy.

936
01:07:34,175 --> 01:07:37,136
I said your mommy's not that fat.
She said she was pregnant.

937
01:07:37,303 --> 01:07:39,222
So it wasn't from her appearance?

938
01:07:39,389 --> 01:07:40,473
No.

939
01:07:40,682 --> 01:07:41,724
Why are you lying?

940
01:07:42,308 --> 01:07:43,476
You're a woman.

941
01:07:43,643 --> 01:07:47,021
You can't tell if a woman is pregnant?

942
01:07:47,230 --> 01:07:49,482
Even if I could tell,

943
01:07:49,649 --> 01:07:52,652
what difference does it make
for Mr. Lavasani?

944
01:07:53,319 --> 01:07:55,488
This woman is his daughter's tutor.

945
01:07:55,655 --> 01:07:57,407
They've fixed their story.

946
01:07:57,657 --> 01:07:59,158
Why are you insulting this lady?

947
01:07:59,367 --> 01:08:00,994
No one's talking to you.

948
01:08:01,536 --> 01:08:03,162
When did I have the opportunity
to fix my story?

949
01:08:03,496 --> 01:08:04,706
I was here last night.

950
01:08:05,081 --> 01:08:08,001
One thing is clear. Now that we are speaking,

951
01:08:08,334 --> 01:08:11,921
that man over there can hear us, can't he?

952
01:08:12,171 --> 01:08:13,506
I didn't hear you.

953
01:08:14,340 --> 01:08:18,344
My mind is on other things.

954
01:08:19,178 --> 01:08:22,265
Why would I listen to your conversation?

955
01:08:22,515 --> 01:08:23,933
Do I have to swear to God?

956
01:08:24,517 --> 01:08:25,768
Like you believe in God!

957
01:08:26,019 --> 01:08:27,854
No, God is for your type only!

958
01:08:28,229 --> 01:08:29,939
Open that window.

959
01:08:32,233 --> 01:08:33,776
He is an honorable man.

960
01:08:33,943 --> 01:08:36,362
I've been going there for a year
to teach his daughter.

961
01:08:37,530 --> 01:08:39,198
He's not like that.

962
01:08:39,532 --> 01:08:42,785
Why should she hide her pregnancy?

963
01:08:43,036 --> 01:08:45,872
If I knew I wouldn't have hired her.

964
01:08:46,039 --> 01:08:49,417
Why did you hire her
without her husband's permission?

965
01:08:50,043 --> 01:08:51,044
Thank you.

966
01:08:51,377 --> 01:08:52,962
You may go.

967
01:08:53,129 --> 01:08:54,213
Thank you.

968
01:08:57,925 --> 01:09:03,723
"During the Sassanid period,
people were divided into two classes,

969
01:09:03,890 --> 01:09:06,225
"the royalty,

970
01:09:06,726 --> 01:09:10,480
"the upper class and the normal people."

971
01:09:10,647 --> 01:09:12,231
"The ordinary people."

972
01:09:16,986 --> 01:09:18,446
What did they ask you?

973
01:09:18,613 --> 01:09:22,492
Whether your dad knew she was pregnant.

974
01:09:22,659 --> 01:09:25,495
Forgive us for taking your time.

975
01:09:25,662 --> 01:09:28,956
There's nothing to forgive.

976
01:09:29,791 --> 01:09:32,085
Sweetie, how did mommy lose her baby?

977
01:09:32,251 --> 01:09:34,128
She got a tummy ache.

978
01:09:35,588 --> 01:09:37,423
Why?

979
01:09:38,091 --> 01:09:40,426
Did Daddy fight With her?

980
01:09:41,094 --> 01:09:43,638
Why should he fight with her?

981
01:09:43,805 --> 01:09:47,850
Maybe because she didn't tell him
she was working in people's homes?

982
01:09:48,017 --> 01:09:51,270
- Did he hit her?
- My mom and dad never fight.

983
01:09:51,938 --> 01:09:56,526
Then why were they fighting
in your drawing that day?

984
01:09:56,693 --> 01:09:58,152
You showed me.

985
01:09:58,319 --> 01:10:00,154
They don't fight anymore.

986
01:10:00,321 --> 01:10:01,948
No?

987
01:10:02,782 --> 01:10:04,325
You're sure?

988
01:10:08,705 --> 01:10:11,541
Yesterday he said
he didn't know she was pregnant.

989
01:10:11,708 --> 01:10:13,960
Now he says he didn't push her.

990
01:10:14,127 --> 01:10:16,546
And you just stand there in silence!

991
01:10:16,838 --> 01:10:19,298
Honestly, didn't you push me?

992
01:10:19,799 --> 01:10:21,467
- I didn't say I...
- Listen...

993
01:10:21,968 --> 01:10:23,845
Don't repeat everything.

994
01:10:24,804 --> 01:10:26,723
How far is the door from the stairs?

995
01:10:26,806 --> 01:10:27,932
2 meters?

996
01:10:28,015 --> 01:10:30,810
What else can have happened to her?

997
01:10:30,893 --> 01:10:32,228
The corridor in our house...

998
01:10:32,395 --> 01:10:33,855
- Look...
- I am talking!

999
01:10:34,063 --> 01:10:35,648
Don't talk. Just answer.

1000
01:10:35,857 --> 01:10:37,024
Quiet!

1001
01:10:37,817 --> 01:10:41,654
You've come here to answer.

1002
01:10:42,405 --> 01:10:44,323
I've a question for you to answer.

1003
01:10:44,490 --> 01:10:45,491
I want to ask him...

1004
01:10:45,700 --> 01:10:46,743
Ask me.

1005
01:10:46,826 --> 01:10:50,204
If you hadn't done anything wrong,
Why'd you come to the hospital

1006
01:10:50,413 --> 01:10:52,331
to see what was wrong with her?

1007
01:10:52,498 --> 01:10:54,041
I came out of decency.

1008
01:10:54,250 --> 01:10:56,335
Where was your decency when you hit her?

1009
01:10:56,502 --> 01:10:58,171
Was anyone there during the fight?

1010
01:10:58,713 --> 01:11:00,006
Their neighbor was there.

1011
01:11:00,506 --> 01:11:01,716
I'll order questionings.

1012
01:11:01,883 --> 01:11:04,927
They're in it too just like the teacher.

1013
01:11:05,052 --> 01:11:07,221
He's been insulting me from the start!

1014
01:11:07,430 --> 01:11:09,182
Am I lying?

1015
01:11:09,348 --> 01:11:11,267
I'll determine who's lying or not.

1016
01:11:11,517 --> 01:11:12,769
You be quiet.

1017
01:11:12,935 --> 01:11:16,397
Sir, do you realize
his ex-wife has posted his bail?

1018
01:11:16,856 --> 01:11:17,857
Oh, my God!

1019
01:11:17,940 --> 01:11:19,400
Can someone vouch for you?

1020
01:11:19,609 --> 01:11:20,735
What do you mean?

1021
01:11:20,902 --> 01:11:23,863
A government employee
or business-owner to vouch for you.

1022
01:11:23,946 --> 01:11:25,782
- No one.
- Why vouch?

1023
01:11:26,032 --> 01:11:27,742
Because she's been accused.

1024
01:11:28,117 --> 01:11:29,202
Accused of what?

1025
01:11:29,619 --> 01:11:32,038
According to the complaint he filed...

1026
01:11:32,246 --> 01:11:33,372
Which he had no right...

1027
01:11:33,539 --> 01:11:36,959
She admitted that she tied his father
to the bed and locked him up.

1028
01:11:37,084 --> 01:11:38,127
I explained to you why.

1029
01:11:38,211 --> 01:11:39,587
Her child just died.

1030
01:11:39,754 --> 01:11:41,297
Keep your voice down.

1031
01:11:43,090 --> 01:11:45,802
Aren't you ashamed?
You call yourself a man?

1032
01:11:46,719 --> 01:11:48,054
I said quiet.

1033
01:11:50,723 --> 01:11:54,894
For God's sake, listen to us for a change.

1034
01:11:55,061 --> 01:11:57,146
He is twisting everything.

1035
01:11:57,814 --> 01:12:00,650
He beat my wife and she had a miscarriage.

1036
01:12:00,900 --> 01:12:03,778
What could be clearer?
Why are you being unjust?

1037
01:12:03,945 --> 01:12:05,071
Listen to us for a change.

1038
01:12:05,238 --> 01:12:08,407
If you disturb the peace,
I'll send you to jail for three clays.

1039
01:12:09,158 --> 01:12:11,577
I've lost everything. You think I fear jail?

1040
01:12:11,744 --> 01:12:13,329
You should fear God.

1041
01:12:14,914 --> 01:12:17,333
Mr. lzadi, call an officer to arrest him.

1042
01:12:17,583 --> 01:12:19,627
Sir, for the sake of the Quran, don't.

1043
01:12:20,753 --> 01:12:23,422
- No, let them come and take me.
- Go out. Be quiet.

1044
01:12:23,589 --> 01:12:26,592
Why be quiet?
So they can trample my rights?

1045
01:12:26,759 --> 01:12:27,927
Go out.

1046
01:12:28,344 --> 01:12:31,013
- Fine, I'm leaving.
- Sir, come out.

1047
01:12:32,640 --> 01:12:33,933
Let me get my helmet.

1048
01:12:34,100 --> 01:12:35,101
Get out.

1049
01:12:36,602 --> 01:12:39,272
I worked for ten years with a cobbler.

1050
01:12:39,438 --> 01:12:42,859
They fired me and said getjustice if you can.

1051
01:12:43,025 --> 01:12:48,197
I sued and went back and forth for a year.
In the end, nothing.

1052
01:12:48,364 --> 01:12:50,116
They said go sit at home.

1053
01:12:51,117 --> 01:12:53,035
But this time I won't let it go.

1054
01:12:53,286 --> 01:12:55,872
This time it's different.

1055
01:12:56,122 --> 01:12:58,833
I have nothing to lose.

1056
01:12:59,000 --> 01:13:01,961
The problem is I can't talk like this guy.

1057
01:13:02,128 --> 01:13:03,796
I am hot-tempered.

1058
01:13:04,297 --> 01:13:05,506
Don't!

1059
01:13:14,640 --> 01:13:15,808
H ojj at?

1060
01:13:17,810 --> 01:13:19,020
I don't feel well.

1061
01:13:20,062 --> 01:13:21,314
Go sit there.

1062
01:13:21,397 --> 01:13:22,398
Let's go)!

1063
01:13:22,481 --> 01:13:25,318
- What do you want? He's calm.
- I have to take him.

1064
01:13:25,484 --> 01:13:27,820
I'm going to talk to the judge.

1065
01:13:27,987 --> 01:13:30,031
Stay there and don't move.

